                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.0031/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-26T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 26, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 26—2:10 p.m]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>326. At his request I had a further conversation with Chamberlain today, report
                    of which goes forward by next pouch.<note n="37" xml:id="d538fn37">Despatch No.
                        2297, June 27; not printed.</note> After emphasizing rapid rate of political
                    deterioration in Europe and the opening caused by Germany’s clearing
                    arrangements, et cetera, he referred to this country’s pending trade agreement
                    negotiations and frankly expressed the fear lest he should be branded with
                    “inconsistency” should they make the contemplated public policy declaration
                    while these trade agreements were in process of negotiation. I felt his attitude
                    as well as Runciman’s reported in my 323, of June 25, 5 p.m., was based on
                    Cabinet consultation and decision to play for time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
